From Scott Dorsey Subject Re Power signal surges in In article Douglas Rand writes In article woof Randall Rhea writes Hams can legally run up to It is very unlikely however that a ham would be running that kind of power from a Ham rigs Not possible You'd need about a amp alternator for just the I can just see You need to slow down on a downgrade so you hit the push to talk Now that indeed is A good friend of mine is running about KW PeP from his Yes he does have a second Yes he calls the rig an electronic brake since the engine noticeably slows when the key is My car unfortunately has so much computer junk under the hood that it's astonishingly sensitive to If I key a HT over the engine with the hood open the car loses timing due to the RF leaking into the distributor Very poor I will however point out that ham radio operators are usually quite willing to help when interference is Remember that any interference is wasted power if I put out in the TV band that's that I am not putting out in the band I am trying to transmit on and can often be the difference between a nice card hanging on the wall and CBers however are usually not as Most illegal CBers however will stop operation when you inform them of a The rest of them will stop operation when you inform the local FCC office of the problem in writing and giving details and addresses Last you can usually tell ham radio Ham operators are required to declare their call sign every so many minutes no more than So if you hear This is or some other call starting with A W or K and no more than total characters you heard a CB'ers probably won't sign I don't know that they're even required to and fire police have other private Good Hams will frequently give their call and will never use a They are less apt to use immense amounts of profanity as well but that's not to say that they don't from time to scott